section.section:
A member is not subject to the requirements of paragraph (1) of this subsection if:
a transfer to the member's treasurer, a continuing political committee, or a slate to which the member belongs or belonged during the 36-month period preceding the filing of the application was made by a political action committee to which an applicant or agent had made a payment;
the applicant or agent made the payment to the political action committee without any intent to subvert the purposes of this subtitle;
the applicant's or agent's payment to the political action committee, and the political action committee's transfer, are disclosed in an affidavit; and
the transfer is returned to the political action committee by the member, or the payment is returned to the applicant or agent by the political action committee.
